1
00:00:00,433 --> 00:00:01,800
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,800 --> 00:00:03,133
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:05,100 --> 00:00:10,500
<i>Calling "Mom, Mom"</i>

4
00:00:11,800 --> 00:00:14,200
<i>I quietly picked and ate them</i>

5
00:00:57,400 --> 00:00:59,000
Isn't that the Chairman's wife?

6
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:01,833
What brings her here again?

7
00:01:08,200 --> 00:01:09,500
Why are you...

8
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:12,800
stomping on that poor blanket?

9
00:01:12,800 --> 00:01:15,100
- Hello.
- Why not use the washing machine...

10
00:01:15,100 --> 00:01:17,000
or go to a laundromat?

11
00:01:17,533 --> 00:01:19,900
I've found this works best
when my mind is troubled.

12
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:22,000
If I just keep stomping away,

13
00:01:22,533 --> 00:01:25,033
it feels like my worries disappear
for a little while.

14
00:01:25,033 --> 00:01:26,500
Those worries of yours.

15
00:01:26,500 --> 00:01:29,833
Why do they only ever cling to you?

16
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:32,400
But what's this?

17
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:36,700
Well, what is it doing there...

18
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:39,500
Looks like herbal medicine.

19
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:42,700
Earlier,

20
00:01:42,700 --> 00:01:45,900
I saw the Chairman's wife in the alley.

21
00:01:46,533 --> 00:01:48,333
Could she have left it behind?

22
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:49,900
What?

23
00:01:50,633 --> 00:01:52,200
She came to my house?

24
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:11,233
She was Yeon Sun.

25
00:02:14,133 --> 00:02:15,500
My daughter, Yeon Sun.

26
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:19,000
My Yeon Sun...

27
00:02:21,133 --> 00:02:22,800
was right in front of me.

28
00:02:24,633 --> 00:02:28,500
How could I not recognize her
all this time?

29
00:02:29,900 --> 00:02:31,133
How could I...

30
00:02:34,433 --> 00:02:35,433
You're right.

31
00:02:36,633 --> 00:02:38,033
That's what most mothers would do.

32
00:02:40,700 --> 00:02:42,033
But some people aren't like that.

33
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:45,500
Sorry?

34
00:02:45,900 --> 00:02:48,200
Some people value their own lives
more than their children.

35
00:02:50,033 --> 00:02:51,033
Their own children...

36
00:02:54,100 --> 00:02:56,600
If people are meant to be connected,
they'll meet eventually...

37
00:02:57,100 --> 00:02:58,500
no matter how far apart they are.

38
00:02:59,700 --> 00:03:02,100
And if they're not,
they won't recognize each other...

39
00:03:02,100 --> 00:03:03,700
even face-to-face.

40
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:08,400
Seeing how much you miss her,

41
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:12,600
I'm sure she's waiting for the day
she can meet you too.

42
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,033
Please don't go.

43
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:17,500
A child abandoned by her mother...

44
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:20,433
is as good as dead
for the rest of her life.

45
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:23,400
If even the mother
who gave birth to her abandons her,

46
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:24,700
where can she go,

47
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:27,100
and how can she ever put down roots?

48
00:03:27,433 --> 00:03:30,200
By the way, your parents...

49
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:32,900
My parents?

50
00:03:34,733 --> 00:03:35,733
I don't have any.

51
00:03:37,833 --> 00:03:41,300
My father passed away before I was born,
so I never knew him.

52
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,000
And my mother...

53
00:03:46,533 --> 00:03:48,133
She passed away a long time ago too.

54
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:53,633
How...

55
00:03:54,300 --> 00:03:56,800
How hard her life must have been.

56
00:03:58,700 --> 00:04:00,600
How deep her resentment must be.

57
00:04:01,900 --> 00:04:04,000
Yeon Sun, I'm sorry.

58
00:04:04,733 --> 00:04:07,200
Mom is...

59
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:09,600
I'm so sorry!

60
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:12,300
Yeon Sun!

61
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:23,400
I'm sorry, I'm so sorry...

62
00:04:26,300 --> 00:04:29,000
What? You can't reach Grandma?

63
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:34,200
She left saying she was going
to the herbal medicine shop,

64
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:38,233
and it's been five hours already.
Her phone is off too.

65
00:04:38,900 --> 00:04:41,233
Has she contacted you by any chance?

66
00:04:41,900 --> 00:04:43,833
No, she hasn't.

67
00:04:45,433 --> 00:04:48,000
All right. I'm sure she'll be back soon.

68
00:04:49,100 --> 00:04:52,300
I'll call you when she gets home,
so don't worry and get back to work.

69
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:53,900
Okay, Grandpa.

70
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:58,033
Where could she have gone?

71
00:04:59,133 --> 00:05:01,233
She has been stopping by our house
these days.

72
00:05:01,233 --> 00:05:03,100
I'll call Mom just in case.

73
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:08,900
Yeah, she definitely came by.

74
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:12,633
Cho Rong's grandma said
she saw her in the alley.

75
00:05:13,733 --> 00:05:16,433
She left a bag of herbal medicine
in the yard.

76
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:18,600
I didn't even know she'd been there.

77
00:05:19,133 --> 00:05:21,300
Okay, Mom.

78
00:05:21,733 --> 00:05:22,833
I'll hang up for now.

79
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:26,800
What's going on?

80
00:05:28,100 --> 00:05:31,200
Why did she come by
and leave without saying anything...

81
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:37,133
She did stop by our house,
but she didn't meet Mom...

82
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:39,900
and only left the bag of herbal medicine
in the yard.

83
00:05:40,700 --> 00:05:43,700
It sounds like she was on her way home
after buying medicine for Grandpa.

84
00:05:44,300 --> 00:05:45,533
But why did she leave it there?

85
00:05:46,233 --> 00:05:49,700
Do you think
she may have found something out?

86
00:05:50,133 --> 00:05:52,100
What? No way.

87
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:54,000
I just have a feeling...

88
00:05:55,133 --> 00:05:56,233
Let's go there.

89
00:05:57,333 --> 00:05:59,400
There? Where...

90
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:13,700
Get me Team Two's information.

91
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:17,500
From then on,
you'll be in the next chairman's camp.

92
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:20,133
I'll show you what it means
to hit the jackpot in life.

93
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:32,700
If it's Cho Eun Ae...

94
00:06:33,733 --> 00:06:35,700
The password she used during Lucky Joy.

95
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:38,500
Okay.

96
00:06:39,533 --> 00:06:40,533
Is this it?

97
00:06:46,933 --> 00:06:47,933
Mr. Han Ji Hun!

98
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:52,033
What are you doing here?

99
00:06:53,100 --> 00:06:54,200
Well...

100
00:06:55,233 --> 00:06:57,500
It looked like Ms. Cho Eun Ae left
without turning off her laptop,

101
00:06:57,800 --> 00:06:58,900
so I was shutting it down for her.

102
00:06:58,900 --> 00:07:00,633
And you expect me to believe that?

103
00:07:05,733 --> 00:07:06,733
I'm sorry.

104
00:07:07,833 --> 00:07:10,500
I was just so curious about how
Team Two's Joy project was progressing.

105
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:13,200
This second round...

106
00:07:14,033 --> 00:07:15,600
will be decided by Joy.

107
00:07:15,900 --> 00:07:16,900
So...

108
00:07:17,833 --> 00:07:19,200
Do you think our team will win...

109
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:21,100
if you steal the other team's information?

110
00:07:22,700 --> 00:07:23,700
No, but...

111
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:27,033
I really want to win this competition.

112
00:07:27,433 --> 00:07:28,900
Don't you, Chief?

113
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:31,933
Of course I want to win.

114
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:35,500
I've put everything in my life on the line
for this competition.

115
00:07:37,333 --> 00:07:38,900
If you want to win that badly,

116
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:42,300
think carefully
about what you should really be doing.

117
00:07:45,333 --> 00:07:46,333
Manager Seo.

118
00:07:47,333 --> 00:07:48,600
Hey, Manager Seo.

119
00:07:49,733 --> 00:07:51,333
Shall we start the meeting in ten minutes?

120
00:07:52,333 --> 00:07:53,500
Yes, sir.

121
00:08:05,033 --> 00:08:08,333
What happened, Yeong Hwa?

122
00:08:08,733 --> 00:08:11,300
I checked the herbal medicine shop...

123
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:13,433
and the market Madam visits,
but I couldn't find her.

124
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:17,433
Then, when I came back,
Madam was lying unconscious at the gate.

125
00:08:17,733 --> 00:08:19,233
My goodness.

126
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:21,200
Mother, are you all right?

127
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:23,200
I'm sorry.

128
00:08:24,100 --> 00:08:26,000
I made you worry, didn't I?

129
00:08:26,033 --> 00:08:27,500
Forget worrying about me.

130
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:29,000
Quick, help her to her room.

131
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:30,000
Yes.

132
00:08:30,700 --> 00:08:31,600
Careful.

133
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:33,833
Goodness, why did this happen?

134
00:08:36,433 --> 00:08:37,700
- Careful.
- My goodness.

135
00:08:38,300 --> 00:08:39,900
What on earth happened?

136
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:43,000
What could have happened to leave someone
who was perfectly fine like this?

137
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:54,600
Yes, Grandpa.

138
00:08:55,633 --> 00:08:57,233
Grandma's back?

139
00:08:59,533 --> 00:09:00,533
Yes.

140
00:09:01,433 --> 00:09:03,700
Do you happen to know where she went?

141
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,933
Yes, Grandpa. Okay.

142
00:09:09,533 --> 00:09:10,700
Your grandma's home?

143
00:09:11,100 --> 00:09:13,200
Thank goodness. That's such a relief.

144
00:09:13,833 --> 00:09:14,833
I know.

145
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,600
I think I got ahead of myself.

146
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:20,133
When I heard she stopped by our house
and only left her bag, I just...

147
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:23,633
I think
I should visit Grandma after work...

148
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:26,433
and ask her what happened today.

149
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:27,600
Okay.

150
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:30,300
What?

151
00:09:30,900 --> 00:09:33,200
You're sure? She's Yeon Sun?

152
00:09:34,100 --> 00:09:36,600
Yes, I'm sure.

153
00:09:39,033 --> 00:09:41,033
I've met her several times.

154
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:45,800
How could I not recognize my own Yeon Sun?

155
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:49,033
Can I even call myself a mother?

156
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:52,733
Am I really her mother?

157
00:10:06,433 --> 00:10:07,433
Mother.

158
00:10:08,133 --> 00:10:09,500
Are you crying?

159
00:10:10,833 --> 00:10:13,400
What is it that's got you so worked up?

160
00:10:13,933 --> 00:10:15,400
Thank you for your concern.

161
00:10:16,233 --> 00:10:17,233
Leave us.

162
00:10:17,933 --> 00:10:20,733
Yes. If you need anything...

163
00:10:23,500 --> 00:10:24,533
Yes, Father.

164
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:27,400
Here.

165
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:30,833
First, have a sip of water...

166
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:32,733
and calm yourself down.

167
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:44,700
So even after seeing the burn scar
on her leg,

168
00:10:44,700 --> 00:10:45,800
you just left?

169
00:10:46,333 --> 00:10:47,633
Without checking anything else?

170
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:54,233
I didn't need to check anything.

171
00:10:55,033 --> 00:10:56,800
I knew immediately.

172
00:10:57,933 --> 00:11:01,400
Her eyes, her lips, even her voice.

173
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:04,300
Everything about her was just Yeon Sun.

174
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:09,033
No wonder she seemed strangely familiar
every time I saw her.

175
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:13,000
Come to think of it, she looked
exactly like the photo Mr. Seo brought.

176
00:11:13,733 --> 00:11:17,533
Why didn't I realize it then?

177
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:22,300
I couldn't recognize her as her mother.
How could you?

178
00:11:22,933 --> 00:11:23,933
Anyway...

179
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:26,700
You should've told her
right then and there.

180
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:27,900
Why did you leave?

181
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:29,733
I couldn't.

182
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:33,200
My sin is too great.

183
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:37,800
I couldn't bring myself
to look her in the eye.

184
00:11:41,633 --> 00:11:42,833
By the time I came to my senses,

185
00:11:44,300 --> 00:11:47,633
I was at the old playground
near the construction site.

186
00:11:49,700 --> 00:11:52,200
It's all right.
Everything's all right now.

187
00:11:52,833 --> 00:11:55,300
Leave the rest to me.

188
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:58,233
What are you going to do?

189
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:00,833
I'll tell her everything...

190
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:03,433
and ask for forgiveness.

191
00:12:04,633 --> 00:12:07,133
I'll even get down on my knees
if I have to.

192
00:12:07,133 --> 00:12:09,300
No. If anyone has to do that,
it should be me.

193
00:12:10,300 --> 00:12:12,200
Until I tell her myself, absolutely...

194
00:12:12,900 --> 00:12:14,933
Each day will feel like an eternity.

195
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:18,100
You've spent 50 years
desperately searching for her.

196
00:12:18,100 --> 00:12:19,233
Why wait any longer?

197
00:12:19,733 --> 00:12:20,733
No...

198
00:12:23,533 --> 00:12:27,933
The resentment in Yeon Sun's heart
runs too deep.

199
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:32,400
And my guilt is just as great.

200
00:12:34,433 --> 00:12:36,400
I don't know how to begin.

201
00:12:38,133 --> 00:12:39,400
Please give me some time.

202
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:43,000
I'll handle it all. I will.

203
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:48,800
There's liriope root, balloon flower root,
and schisandra berries.

204
00:12:48,800 --> 00:12:50,800
They're all herbs
that help protect the lungs.

205
00:12:51,333 --> 00:12:54,300
I think she stopped by while bringing
medicine home for the Chairman.

206
00:12:54,833 --> 00:12:57,000
I don't know why she left it at our house,

207
00:12:57,700 --> 00:12:58,800
but please return it to her.

208
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:00,100
Yes, I will.

209
00:13:00,400 --> 00:13:02,633
And I'll stay
at my parents' house tonight.

210
00:13:03,433 --> 00:13:05,000
All right. Do that.

211
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:08,900
Bit Na,
how about sleeping with Dad tonight?

212
00:13:09,100 --> 00:13:10,300
I'd love that!

213
00:13:11,300 --> 00:13:13,200
You don't have to worry about that.

214
00:13:13,300 --> 00:13:15,700
It's not like you're staying here
for free. I feel bad.

215
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:17,700
Not at all. Then I'll be off.

216
00:13:26,533 --> 00:13:29,233
Where has he been all day?
He hasn't come by once.

217
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:31,600
He even left the fish starving.

218
00:13:36,300 --> 00:13:37,300
Bung Wu, Bung Nim.

219
00:13:37,900 --> 00:13:39,900
Isn't your owner
being a little irresponsible?

220
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:43,733
What are you doing to my pet fish?

221
00:13:43,900 --> 00:13:45,100
I fed them.

222
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:48,900
You brought them as pets, but you can't
even keep track of their feeding time.

223
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:50,833
Do you even know
what being a pet owner means?

224
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:52,133
What?

225
00:13:52,733 --> 00:13:54,800
- You fed them just now?
- Yes.

226
00:13:55,300 --> 00:13:57,500
They're actually in their fasting period.

227
00:13:57,633 --> 00:13:58,900
Fasting? Why?

228
00:14:00,033 --> 00:14:03,333
Goldfish need to fast regularly
once a week...

229
00:14:03,333 --> 00:14:06,533
to prevent swim bladder disease
and improve digestion.

230
00:14:06,833 --> 00:14:08,400
You really don't know anything.

231
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:11,733
Then you should've told me beforehand.

232
00:14:12,133 --> 00:14:14,300
My bad, Bung Wu, Bung Nim.

233
00:14:14,300 --> 00:14:15,333
I'm sorry.

234
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:20,900
It's not like it'll be a disaster
just because it happened once.

235
00:14:21,433 --> 00:14:23,100
I'll let it slide this time.

236
00:14:23,300 --> 00:14:24,700
You'll let it slide?

237
00:14:24,700 --> 00:14:26,333
For me? You?

238
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:30,300
Right.

239
00:14:30,333 --> 00:14:31,533
Did you hear from Hye Ji?

240
00:14:31,533 --> 00:14:33,500
About what happened
between you two that night?

241
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:35,200
Yes, I did.

242
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:36,200
That's actually why I'm bringing it up.

243
00:14:36,400 --> 00:14:38,233
I think you may have misunderstood.

244
00:14:38,300 --> 00:14:40,200
Misunderstood? No way.

245
00:14:42,233 --> 00:14:44,333
You mean how Hye Ji asked you
if you should start dating that day,

246
00:14:44,333 --> 00:14:46,000
and you said okay?

247
00:14:46,900 --> 00:14:48,100
What about it?

248
00:14:48,100 --> 00:14:50,100
You two should give it a shot.
You look good together.

249
00:14:50,100 --> 00:14:52,833
No, that's a complete misunderstanding.

250
00:14:52,833 --> 00:14:55,600
I'm saying you should
give things a shot with Oh Hye Ji.

251
00:14:55,733 --> 00:14:56,733
What...

252
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:03,533
You punk! Do it right!

253
00:15:04,733 --> 00:15:05,933
Here we go again.

254
00:15:08,600 --> 00:15:11,200
Yu Jin Seok! Who told you to sit down?

255
00:15:11,933 --> 00:15:14,700
You're the youngest in the ER.
How dare you sit?

256
00:15:15,133 --> 00:15:17,533
Looks like we need
to toughen you up again.

257
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:20,000
Sit. Stand.

258
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,900
Sit. Stand!

259
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:25,500
(Agreement on Child Custody
and Parental Rights)

260
00:15:25,500 --> 00:15:27,233
(Visitation Location
to Be Mutually Agreed Upon)

261
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:31,433
Goodness, people can fall into debt
or go bankrupt in life.

262
00:15:32,100 --> 00:15:33,700
You two are still young.

263
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:36,233
You should work hard and pay it off.

264
00:15:36,700 --> 00:15:38,633
Why would she choose...

265
00:15:39,233 --> 00:15:40,800
to shoulder that debt all by herself?

266
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:44,100
Her guilt is overwhelming.

267
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:47,500
I tried persuading her
to pay off the debt together,

268
00:15:48,500 --> 00:15:50,833
but she said that would be even worse
for Bit Na.

269
00:15:51,900 --> 00:15:53,633
She doesn't want Bit Na...

270
00:15:53,900 --> 00:15:55,533
to see her constantly struggling
over money anymore.

271
00:15:56,800 --> 00:15:58,900
For Ji Seon to choose divorce...

272
00:15:59,900 --> 00:16:01,200
with that state of mind,

273
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:03,800
she must've been truly desperate.

274
00:16:04,733 --> 00:16:05,933
You should head upstairs now.

275
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:09,333
Bit Na must be waiting,
excited to sleep with her dad.

276
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:11,200
- Yes, Dad. Good night.
- All right.

277
00:16:14,700 --> 00:16:15,700
Hey, what's wrong?

278
00:16:15,900 --> 00:16:17,800
Are you hurt somewhere?

279
00:16:18,600 --> 00:16:22,233
You've been leaving early
every morning lately. Don't tell me...

280
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:25,433
Yes, I started another job
in the mornings.

281
00:16:26,100 --> 00:16:28,400
That's why I haven't been able
to take Bit Na to kindergarten lately.

282
00:16:29,100 --> 00:16:31,033
Another job? What kind?

283
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:32,300
Loading and unloading delivery trucks.

284
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:34,900
The pay is pretty good for part-time work,

285
00:16:35,433 --> 00:16:37,933
and the hours fit
before my afternoon academy classes.

286
00:16:39,133 --> 00:16:41,633
I need to save up quickly
and get a house for Bit Na.

287
00:16:42,533 --> 00:16:43,533
Good night.

288
00:17:06,933 --> 00:17:07,933
Bit Na.

289
00:17:08,233 --> 00:17:09,433
Doesn't meditation...

290
00:17:09,933 --> 00:17:12,300
make all the unnecessary thoughts
in your heart...

291
00:17:12,600 --> 00:17:14,000
disappear?

292
00:17:15,100 --> 00:17:16,133
Yeah, Dad.

293
00:17:18,100 --> 00:17:19,200
Then now,

294
00:17:19,833 --> 00:17:21,733
Dad has something to say...

295
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:25,100
to the calm and peaceful Bit Na.

296
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:27,433
Are you ready to listen?

297
00:17:30,833 --> 00:17:32,100
Mom and Dad...

298
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:36,133
got divorced.

299
00:17:38,633 --> 00:17:41,700
I'm sorry for hurting you, Bit Na.

300
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:46,500
Even though Mom and Dad have separated
and don't live together anymore,

301
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:51,100
Mom will always be your mom.

302
00:17:51,100 --> 00:17:53,400
That will never, ever change.

303
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:55,100
And one more thing.

304
00:17:55,800 --> 00:17:56,900
Mom and Dad...

305
00:17:58,100 --> 00:18:00,300
love you more than anything in the world.

306
00:18:01,533 --> 00:18:02,633
Me too.

307
00:18:03,233 --> 00:18:07,200
I love Mom and Dad
more than anything in the world too.

308
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:09,700
Thank you. Thank you so much.

309
00:18:11,200 --> 00:18:13,433
Mom is busy with work right now,

310
00:18:13,433 --> 00:18:14,933
so she can't come see you for a while,

311
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:19,100
but she promised you can see her
whenever you miss her.

312
00:18:19,833 --> 00:18:21,000
So wait just a little longer.

313
00:18:22,900 --> 00:18:26,233
Mom never left you.

314
00:18:27,300 --> 00:18:31,100
You're always shining brightly
in Mom's heart.

315
00:18:32,900 --> 00:18:35,533
Dad, can I cry?

316
00:18:40,700 --> 00:18:41,700
Of course.

317
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:44,533
Cry as much as you want.

318
00:18:47,033 --> 00:18:48,033
It's okay.

319
00:18:49,600 --> 00:18:51,500
Everything's okay. It's okay. Cry.

320
00:18:56,700 --> 00:18:59,300
So you're saying
you have no idea what happened?

321
00:18:59,433 --> 00:19:00,433
No.

322
00:19:00,833 --> 00:19:02,033
She came home looking half dead,

323
00:19:02,033 --> 00:19:05,300
went straight into her room,
and cried her eyes out.

324
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:08,300
And she hasn't moved since.

325
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:10,833
Goodness. What on earth happened?

326
00:19:12,100 --> 00:19:14,800
Could it be like last time?
Maybe she met...

327
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:16,300
another fake daughter or something.

328
00:19:16,300 --> 00:19:17,300
No way.

329
00:19:17,300 --> 00:19:18,900
If that were the case,
wouldn't Father know?

330
00:19:20,300 --> 00:19:23,800
Do you think she might've realized
who her real daughter is?

331
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:26,600
I thought about that too,

332
00:19:27,133 --> 00:19:29,633
but if that were true,
would things be this quiet?

333
00:19:30,333 --> 00:19:32,700
That family would've stormed in here,

334
00:19:32,933 --> 00:19:34,700
or the two of them
would've rushed over there.

335
00:19:35,033 --> 00:19:36,200
There would've been chaos.

336
00:19:37,033 --> 00:19:38,400
No. That can't be it.

337
00:19:38,500 --> 00:19:41,233
Right. It can't be. No way.

338
00:19:41,433 --> 00:19:42,433
I'm here.

339
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:45,133
Gyeol! What brings you here?

340
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:48,000
Well. I came to see Grandma.

341
00:19:48,500 --> 00:19:49,633
Is she inside?

342
00:19:49,633 --> 00:19:51,133
Grandma isn't feeling well.

343
00:19:51,933 --> 00:19:53,500
Hey, but isn't that...

344
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:55,233
Grandma's shopping bag?

345
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:58,600
I'll just say hello and come right out.

346
00:20:01,733 --> 00:20:02,733
Unbelievable.

347
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:05,400
Why does Gyeol have Mother's shopping bag?

348
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:09,800
Is Eun Ae's mother
really Grandma's daughter?

349
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:15,000
We had a feeling,
and it turns out we were right.

350
00:20:16,533 --> 00:20:18,533
You suspected it?

351
00:20:18,900 --> 00:20:22,000
Yes. Eun Ae told me her mother...

352
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:24,500
had the exact same necklace as...

353
00:20:24,700 --> 00:20:26,100
the one Grandma uploaded to the Joy app.

354
00:20:27,133 --> 00:20:28,133
So Yeon Sun still had...

355
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:31,400
that necklace.

356
00:20:31,933 --> 00:20:33,933
Now the two of you just need to meet.

357
00:20:34,733 --> 00:20:37,500
But Eun Ae's mother has severe trauma.

358
00:20:38,100 --> 00:20:41,300
Eun Ae has suggested looking
for her grandmother several times,

359
00:20:41,833 --> 00:20:42,900
but she always refused.

360
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:45,700
I was prepared for that.

361
00:20:46,733 --> 00:20:49,800
Still, they need to meet soon.

362
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:52,100
What should we do now?

363
00:20:52,300 --> 00:20:54,200
I'd like to tell her immediately,

364
00:20:54,900 --> 00:20:56,433
but your Grandma asked for some time.

365
00:20:57,100 --> 00:20:58,200
She wants to tell her herself.

366
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:00,833
After finding out today,

367
00:21:01,333 --> 00:21:03,700
she couldn't even drink water
after getting home...

368
00:21:04,833 --> 00:21:08,433
and only just managed to fall asleep
after taking a sleeping pill.

369
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:47,733
Just as expected.

370
00:21:53,800 --> 00:21:55,000
Do you think running away from this...

371
00:21:55,433 --> 00:21:57,400
will erase what you did?

372
00:21:58,433 --> 00:22:01,700
The disciplinary process will be held soon
according to company policy.

373
00:22:02,200 --> 00:22:04,133
Disciplinary action?

374
00:22:05,100 --> 00:22:06,133
Manager Seo.

375
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:08,600
I was only following orders, Manager.

376
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:10,700
Following orders?

377
00:22:12,900 --> 00:22:15,400
Are you saying
someone instructed you to do this?

378
00:22:19,333 --> 00:22:22,433
Who told you to do this?

379
00:22:24,233 --> 00:22:25,300
I'm asking who it was!

380
00:22:25,900 --> 00:22:27,033
I can't tell you.

381
00:22:28,100 --> 00:22:31,000
All I can say is that Team One...

382
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:34,633
was given orders to win the second round
by any means necessary.

383
00:22:36,300 --> 00:22:37,300
Orders.

384
00:22:39,300 --> 00:22:41,100
Hand me the USB and go home.

385
00:22:41,500 --> 00:22:44,700
I'll think about how to handle this
and make a decision soon.

386
00:22:50,300 --> 00:22:51,900
Manager, my mother is a widow,
and I'm her only son.

387
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:55,800
My mother is fighting an illness,
so if something happens to me too...

388
00:22:56,400 --> 00:22:57,500
Didn't I tell you to leave?

389
00:22:58,800 --> 00:22:59,900
Please, just this once.

390
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:02,800
If this goes
before the disciplinary committee,

391
00:23:03,933 --> 00:23:05,800
I'll have no choice
but to tell the whole truth.

392
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:07,700
And then the fallout
will be impossible to contain.

393
00:23:07,700 --> 00:23:08,700
Mr. Han Ji Hun!

394
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:16,300
Yes. I'm sorry, Manager.

395
00:23:33,500 --> 00:23:36,700
I think something's up with your dad.

396
00:23:37,233 --> 00:23:39,200
- Sorry?
- Last time,

397
00:23:39,200 --> 00:23:42,000
remember that man we saw
when I went to give you those documents?

398
00:23:42,500 --> 00:23:44,233
The man Dad said he didn't know.

399
00:23:45,600 --> 00:23:46,600
What about him?

400
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:48,033
Ever since that day,

401
00:23:48,500 --> 00:23:51,133
your dad's been acting like
he's being chased, anxious all the time.

402
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:53,400
He's even sleeping in the study now.

403
00:23:54,233 --> 00:23:55,700
I overheard him earlier.

404
00:23:56,433 --> 00:23:58,500
I think he made plans
to meet someone tomorrow.

405
00:23:58,933 --> 00:24:00,300
- Tomorrow?
- Yeah.

406
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:05,000
I wrote down a number
that I think belongs to that man,

407
00:24:05,533 --> 00:24:07,200
but I can't just call him out of the blue.

408
00:24:08,633 --> 00:24:10,700
Mom, you know Dad.

409
00:24:10,900 --> 00:24:13,200
He's not the kind of person
who'd get involved in something bad.

410
00:24:13,633 --> 00:24:15,533
Don't worry too much and get some sleep.

411
00:24:16,933 --> 00:24:18,900
Right, you're probably right.

412
00:24:19,933 --> 00:24:21,033
It's probably nothing.

413
00:24:22,300 --> 00:24:23,300
Yeah, get some sleep.

414
00:24:30,700 --> 00:24:32,600
(Kangsu Construction)

415
00:24:33,500 --> 00:24:34,633
What's going on?

416
00:24:34,633 --> 00:24:36,700
You actually called me out during work.

417
00:24:36,933 --> 00:24:39,433
- Was it you?
- What?

418
00:24:39,633 --> 00:24:43,533
The person who told Han Ji Hun
to steal Team Two's Joy upgrade file.

419
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:45,433
Was it you, Chief?

420
00:24:46,633 --> 00:24:47,633
What are you talking about?

421
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:50,200
Even if you felt threatened
by this competition,

422
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:53,333
- isn't this going too far?
- Seo Seung Ri!

423
00:24:53,333 --> 00:24:56,800
I know you've always felt inferior
to Team Manager Ko...

424
00:24:57,100 --> 00:24:58,300
since you were young,

425
00:24:58,900 --> 00:25:00,300
but did you really have to go this far?

426
00:25:00,933 --> 00:25:02,600
What? Inferior?

427
00:25:03,900 --> 00:25:04,900
So what you're saying is,

428
00:25:05,500 --> 00:25:07,000
I thought I'd lose to Gyeol,

429
00:25:07,700 --> 00:25:09,600
so I did something that underhanded
out of jealousy?

430
00:25:10,100 --> 00:25:11,700
If it wasn't you, then who was it?

431
00:25:12,433 --> 00:25:14,100
Who else would order Han Ji Hun
to do something like that?

432
00:25:14,800 --> 00:25:15,800
Forget it.

433
00:25:17,333 --> 00:25:18,500
Believe whatever you want.

434
00:25:19,533 --> 00:25:21,600
It seems you've already decided the answer
before calling me out here.

435
00:25:24,600 --> 00:25:27,433
Could you leave now? I'd like to be alone.

436
00:25:27,733 --> 00:25:28,733
Chief.

437
00:25:52,233 --> 00:25:53,233
Dad?

438
00:25:57,000 --> 00:25:59,400
Go ahead.
What information did you want to tell me?

439
00:26:01,533 --> 00:26:03,000
Where should I start?

440
00:26:04,700 --> 00:26:06,633
Back when I ran the diner,

441
00:26:07,833 --> 00:26:09,300
I had a lot of gambling debt.

442
00:26:10,200 --> 00:26:13,900
There was no way I could repay it,
so I fled in the middle of the night.

443
00:26:15,633 --> 00:26:17,733
The people who said
they'd come get Yeon Sun...

444
00:26:17,733 --> 00:26:19,800
stopped contacting me for over a month.

445
00:26:20,100 --> 00:26:21,300
I couldn't just leave the child alone,

446
00:26:22,133 --> 00:26:25,900
so I put her in an orphanage
for the time being.

447
00:26:26,600 --> 00:26:27,600
And then?

448
00:26:27,800 --> 00:26:30,600
It's about finding
the Chairman's daughter.

449
00:26:32,233 --> 00:26:33,233
I can't talk for free.

450
00:26:33,300 --> 00:26:36,533
I'll compensate you
for information I don't already know,

451
00:26:37,200 --> 00:26:38,300
but everything you've told me so far,
I already knew.

452
00:26:39,600 --> 00:26:40,600
Really?

453
00:26:41,700 --> 00:26:44,833
Then the next thing I tell you
will make your eyes pop.

454
00:26:45,100 --> 00:26:47,400
Is it that she was adopted in France?

455
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:51,100
The adoption was annulled five years later
and she returned to Korea. Then what?

456
00:26:53,233 --> 00:26:54,900
You're a chief assistant
at a major corporation.

457
00:26:55,700 --> 00:26:57,900
I guess you already knew that much.

458
00:26:59,400 --> 00:27:01,400
I got a call
when the adoption was annulled.

459
00:27:02,433 --> 00:27:04,133
They asked if I wanted to raise her again.

460
00:27:04,500 --> 00:27:05,933
Of course I said no.

461
00:27:06,300 --> 00:27:09,033
I could barely support my wife as it was.

462
00:27:10,533 --> 00:27:11,733
Is that all?

463
00:27:12,800 --> 00:27:14,400
Then I have nothing to gain from this.

464
00:27:15,333 --> 00:27:17,100
So,

465
00:27:18,000 --> 00:27:19,700
because you already know everything,

466
00:27:20,633 --> 00:27:23,333
I shouldn't expect any compensation
from you?

467
00:27:26,600 --> 00:27:28,100
Well, if that's the case, so be it.

468
00:27:30,100 --> 00:27:31,100
But tell me this.

469
00:27:32,600 --> 00:27:35,933
Does the Chairman you serve,
or anyone at the company...

470
00:27:38,600 --> 00:27:41,700
Do your wife and daughter I saw
in the lobby know?

471
00:27:42,400 --> 00:27:44,100
That you and I go way back?

472
00:27:44,300 --> 00:27:45,333
Jeong Dong Pal!

473
00:27:46,500 --> 00:27:47,500
That's right.

474
00:27:48,633 --> 00:27:49,933
It's me.

475
00:27:51,233 --> 00:27:53,300
Dong Pal. Jeong Dong Pal.

476
00:27:56,100 --> 00:27:58,900
The guy with a nose for money.

477
00:28:01,900 --> 00:28:04,600
Just prepare one big bill. Then I'll...

478
00:28:05,700 --> 00:28:09,000
keep my mouth shut forever
about your criminal record.

479
00:28:09,933 --> 00:28:11,100
Keep that mouth shut!

480
00:28:25,300 --> 00:28:26,833
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
